ent, and coordinate liaison between the [[Hong Kong government]] and the relevant [[mainland China]] authorities, as well as to promote various regional cooperation initiatives between Hong Kong and the mainland. Prior to 2007, this post was known as the Secretary for Constitutional Affairs.\n\n==List of office holders==\n'''Political party:''' {{legend2|{{Nonpartisan/meta/color}}|[[Nonpartisan]]|border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n\n===Deputy Chief Secretaries, 1985\u20131989===\n{|class=\"wikitable\"  style=\"text-align:left\"\n|-\n! width=10px| No.\n! width=80px| Portrait\n! width=180px| Name\n! width=180px colspan=2| Term of office\n! width=120px|[[Governor of Hong Kong|Governor]]\n! Ref\n|-\n| rowspan=2 align=center| 1 || rowspan=2| [[File:No image.svg|80px]] || rowspan=2| [[Alan James Scott]]<br>\u65bd\u606a || rowspan=2| 10 June 1985 || rowspan=2| 22 March 1987 || Sir [[Edward Youde]]<br>{{small|(1982\u20131986)}} || rowspan=2|<ref name=\"gaz1986\">{{cite journal |title=G.N. 3478 of 1985 |journal=Hong Kong Government Gazette |date=25 October 1985 |volume=132|page=4813}}</ref><ref name=\"gaz19870327\">{{cite journal |title=G.N. 955 of 1987 |journal=Hong Kong Government Gazette |date=10 March 1989 |volume=132|pages=1373, 1480}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=2| Sir [[David Clive Wilson|David Wilson]]<br>{{small|(1987\u20131992)}} \n|-\n| align=center| 2 || [[File:John Chan.jpg|80px]] || [[John Chan]]<br>\u9673\u7956\u6fa4 || 23 March 1987 || 28 February 1989 || <ref name=\"gaz19870327\"/><ref name=\"gaz198903\">{{cite journal |title=G.N. 730 of 1989 |journal=Hong Kong Government Gazette |date=10 March 1989 |volume=132|pages=1072, 1123}}</ref>\n|-\n|}\n\n===Secretaries for Constitutional Affairs, 1989\u20131997===\n{|class=\"wikitable\"  style=\"text-align:left\"\n|-\n! width=10px| No.\n! width=80px| Portrait\n! width=180px| Name\n! width=180px colspan=2| Term of office\n! width=120px|[[Governor of Hong Kong|Governor]]\n! Ref\n|-\n| align=center| 1 || [[File:Michael Suen Ming Yeu